@startuml
title Math Values - Practical Flow

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

class Vector2 {
	+ x
	+ y
}

class Vector3
class Vector4
class Rect2D {
	+ position
	+ size
}
class Matrix
class Quaternion
class ApproxValue

class Widget
class Mesh
class RenderCommand
class Tests

Widget --> Vector2 : position and size
Widget --> Rect2D : local/global bounds
Mesh --> Vector2 : 2D vertices
Mesh --> Vector3 : 3D-compatible data
RenderCommand --> Matrix : transforms when needed
RenderCommand --> Quaternion : orientation math when needed
Tests --> ApproxValue : tolerant comparisons

note bottom
The math layer provides plain value types used by
widgets, rendering data, and tests.
end note

@enduml
